DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
);
 
TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

# generate a random starting point
$x0 = random(1,3,1);
$y0 = random(3,6,1);

# and an increment
$dx = random(.1,.5,.1);
$dy = random(.1,.5,.1);
$dy += 0.1 if ( $dx == $dy );

# so the ending point is
$x1 = $x0 + $dx;
$y1 = $y0 + $dy;

# and the power for the first question is
$r = random(2,5,1);

# the graph
$figure = image( "figQ51.gif", tex_size=>450 );

BEGIN_TEXT

If \( (x_0, y_0) = ($x0, $y0) \) and \( (x_1, y_1) = ($x1, $y1) \), 
use the following graph to find the indicated derivatives
$PAR
$BCENTER
$figure
$BR
${BITALIC}(Click on the graph to get a larger version.)$EITALIC
$ECENTER

$PAR
If \( h(x)=(f(x))^{$r} \), \( h'($x0) = \) \{ ans_rule(25) \}
$BR
If \( g(x)=f^{-1}(x) \), \( g'($y0) = \) \{ ans_rule(25) \}

END_TEXT


ANS( num_cmp( "$r*($y0^($r - 1))*($y1-$y0)/($x1-$x0)" ) );
ANS( num_cmp( "($x1-$x0)/($y1-$y0)" ) );

$m = round(100*$dy/$dx)/100;
$r1p = ($r == 2) ? '' : '^{' . ($r-1) . '}';
$ans1 = round(100*$r*($y0**($r - 1))*($y1-$y0)/($x1-$x0))/100;


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Since the point \(($x0,$y0)\) is on the curve, we know \(f($x0)=$y0\).
The point \(($x1,$y1)\) is on the tangent line, so
\[ 
  \hbox{Slope of tangent} = \frac{$y1-$y0}{$x1-$x0} = \frac{$dy}{$dx} = $m. 
 \]
Thus, \(f'($x0)=$m\).
$PAR
By the chain rule
\[
h'($x0) = $r(f($x0))$r1p\cdot f'($x0) =$r\cdot $y0$r1p\cdot $m = $ans1.
 \]

$PAR

Because \( g(x) \) is the inverse function of \( f \), we know that 
\( g($y0) = $x0 \).  Then note that \( f(g(x)) = f(f^{-1}(x)) = x \),
so \( f(g(x)) = x \).  Differentiating both sides of the equation, 
\( f'(g(x))\cdot g'(x) = 1 \), so \( g'(x) = \frac{1}{f'(g(x))} \).
Thus 
\( g'($y0) = \frac{1}{f'(g($y0))} = \frac{1}{f'($x0)} = \frac1{$m} \).

END_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();
